# Section 1 – Sync Offence Notice and Offender data between the Intranet and Internet Zones for payment

## Use case

- OCMS shall enable the retrieval of all outstanding Parking Offence Notices, including both payable and non-payable notices, through the following Internet-based payment channels to facilitate payment by motorists:URA eService – Payment of Fines
- AXS
- To facilitate the use case, OCMS will use the concurrent update method to synchronize Parking Offence Notices between the Intranet and Internet Zones.

- The method works by:A cron job runs periodically from the Intranet system to pull newly-created Notices from the Internet database and synchronize them into the Intranet database.
- Using API to update an existing notice in the Internet database in real-time immediately after the notice has been modified/updated in the Intranet.
- When a Notice is marked as paid in the Internet, the Intranet system will pull the updated payment status via the cron job and update the corresponding record in the Intranet database accordingly.

- This method ensures that the Notice data in the Intranet and Internet Zones are always consistent. 

- This in turns ensures that the URA eService and AXS payment channels are always retrieving the most updated notices when users initiate payment on the platforms.

## Intranet Push to Internet

![](data:image/png;base64,)

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Start | Entry point of the process flow | The workflow begins here. |
| Insert into intranet table | Add a new record to the intranet database | Data is inserted into the intranet table for processing. |
| Success? (Intranet insert) | Decision point to check intranet insertion status | Verifies whether the intranet table insert was successful. |
| Response error | Return an error response | If the intranet insert fails, an error response is returned and the process stops. |
| Insert into internet table | Add a new record to the internet database | Data from the intranet is inserted into the internet table. |
| Success? (Internet insert) | Decision point to check internet insertion status | Verifies whether the internet table insert was successful. |
| Log error | Record an error in logs | If the internet insert fails, the error is logged and the process stops. |
| Patch is_sync intranet table to true | Update intranet table record | Marks the record in the intranet table as synchronized. |
| Response success | Return a success response | Indicates successful completion of the synchronization process. |
| End | Exit point of the process flow | The workflow ends here. |

### Success Outcome

- Data is successfully inserted into the intranet table.
- Data is successfully inserted into the internet table.
- The intranet table record is updated with is_sync set to true.
- A success response is returned to indicate completion.
- The workflow reaches the End state without triggering any error-handling paths.
### Error Handling

| Error Scenario | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Intranet insert failure | The insert into the intranet table is not successful | Flow goes to response error and then End |
| Internet insert failure | The insert into the internet table is not successful | Flow goes to log error and then End |

## Cron Retry Intranet Push to Internet

![](data:image/png;base64,)

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Cron Start | Entry point for scheduled execution | The process is triggered by a scheduled cron job. |
| Query intranet table which records need to sync, filter by is_sync = false | Retrieve unsynchronized records from intranet | Reads intranet records where is_sync flag is set to false. |
| Success? (Intranet query) | Decision point to check if query succeeded | Verifies whether the query to fetch unsynced records was successful. |
| Log error | Record error for troubleshooting | Logs details of the failed query into application log for later analysis. |
| Transform &amp; validate for internet schema | Prepare data to match target schema | Remove all fields not inside the internet table; make sure all required fields already have values. |
| Push to internet | Insert or send data to internet database/system | Transfers retrieved intranet records to the internet database. Insert into the Internet database using insert-only, unique-PK semantics: If the PK doesn’t exist → insert the row. If the PK already exists → treat as update. |
| Success? (Push to internet) | Decision point to check if push succeeded | Verifies whether data transfer to the internet database/system was successful or already exist. |
| Log error | Record error for troubleshooting | Logs details of the failed push into application log for later analysis. |
| Patch is_sync intranet table to true | Update synchronization status | Sets is_sync flag to true in intranet records that were successfully pushed to the internet. |
| Response success | Return a success message | Confirms that synchronization was completed without errors. |
| End | Exit point of the process flow | Marks the termination of the cron job workflow. |

### Data Mapping

Refer to section 1.3.2

### Success Outcome

- Cron job starts the workflow.
- Intranet is queried for records where is_sync = false.
- Records are pushed to the internet.
- Intranet records are patched with is_sync = true.
- A success response is returned.
- The workflow ends without triggering any error path.
### Error Handling

| Error Scenario | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Intranet query failure | The query for records with is_sync = false is not successful | The flow log the error to application log and ends. |
| Push to internet failure | The operation that pushes data to the internet system is not successful | The flow log the error to application log and ends. |

## Intranet Update

![](data:image/png;base64,)

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Start | Entry point of the process flow | The workflow begins here. |
| Update into intranet table | Update an existing record in the intranet database | Executes an update on the intranet table. |
| Update into internet table | Update an existing record in the internet database | Executes an update on the internet table. |
| Both success? | Decision point to verify update success | Checks if both intranet and internet updates were successful. |
| Response success | Return a success message | Sent if both updates succeed. |
| Rollback update | Reverse the changes made during update | Reverts both intranet and internet updates when either or both fail, ensuring a complete rollback of all related changes. |
| Response error | Return an error message | Sent after rollback to indicate failure. |
| End | Exit point of the process flow | Marks the termination of the process. |

### Data Mapping

#### Offender Table

| Zone | Database Table | Field Name |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Intranet | ocms_offence_notice_owner_driver | Refer to OCMS data dictionary for the data fields within the ONOD table |
| Internet (PII) | eocms_offence_notice_owner_driver | Refer to OCMS data dictionary for the data fields within the eONOD table |

### Success Outcome

- Update into intranet table completes.
- Update into internet table completes.
- Both success? evaluates to yes.
- Response success is returned.
- Workflow reaches End without entering the rollback path.
### Error Handling

| Error Scenario | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Any update fails | Either the intranet update or the internet update is not successful | Flow goes to rollback update, then response error, then End. |

## End Day Sync Check

![](data:image/png;base64,)

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Cron summary batch job | Process initiation | The scheduled job triggers the end-day sync process. |
| Retrieve internet table eocms_web_txn_detail | Data extraction | Fetch records from the internet-side transaction table where is_sync = false and status = S. |
| Any record? | Record check | Decision point to verify if eligible records are found. |
| Log no record | No data outcome | If no records exist, log the result and move to status update. |
| Update/insert to intranet table ocms_web_txn_detail | Data sync to intranet | Insert or update the retrieved records into the intranet transaction table. |
| Any fail record(s)? (intranet) | Intranet validation | Check if there are any failed transactions during insert/update to the intranet table. |
| Log error (intranet) | Failure handling | If failures occurred during intranet update, log the error and continue. |
| Update internet table | Data sync confirmation | Update the internet-side transaction table to mark records as synced: is_sync = true, upd_date = today. |
| Any fail record(s)? (internet) | Internet validation | Check if there are any failures during the internet table update. |
| Log error (internet) | Failure handling | If failures occurred during the internet update, log the error and continue. |
| Update status cron in ocms_batch_job | Status update | Update the cron job status in the batch job table regardless of earlier outcomes. |
| Summary batch job report process | Reporting | Generate a summary report of the batch job run (refer to OCMS 7 Technical Document). |

### Data Mapping

#### Intranet Push to Internet

Refer to Section 1.3.1

#### Intranet Pull update from Internet

### Success Outcome

- Records retrieved – Eligible transactions (is_sync = false and status = S) are successfully fetched from the internet transaction table.
- Records synced to intranet – The system successfully inserts or updates the retrieved transactions into the intranet table ocms_web_txn_detail.
- Internet table updated – The internet transaction table eocms_web_txn_detail is updated with is_sync = true and upd_date = today for all processed records.
- No sync errors detected – The process confirms that both intranet and internet updates complete without failures.
- Status updated – The cron job status in ocms_batch_job is successfully updated to reflect the sync completion.
- Summary report generated – A summary batch job report is created, in line with the OCMS 7 Technical Document.
- Process completed – The end-day sync finishes successfully, with all eligible records synchronized and logged appropriately.
### Error Handling

| Error Scenario | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| No record found | No eligible transactions retrieved from eocms_web_txn_detail | When the query returns no rows (is_sync = false and status = S), the process logs “no record” before moving to status update. |
| Intranet update/insert failure | Failure while updating/inserting into ocms_web_txn_detail | If errors occur during the intranet table sync, the process logs the error, then proceeds to the status update step. |
| Internet update failure | Failure while updating eocms_web_txn_detail | If the internet table update (setting is_sync = true and upd_date = today) fails, the error is logged before continuing to the status update step. |

# Section 2 – Update payment status from Internet to Intranet

## Use Case

- When a notice is successfully paid via the eService or AXS:OCMS updates the notice’s payment status in the Internet database
- OCMS records the transaction details (e.g. payment date/time, method, and receipt number) in the Internet database
- The updated payment status and transaction details in the Internet are then synchronized to the Intranet database to keep the data in both environments aligned.
- The OCMS Internet backend will send the payment status update to the Intranet via cron in Intranet backend.
- During processing of the data retrieved from the Internet database, the OCMS Intranet backend will:Verify that the notice details from the Internet match the corresponding notice in the Intranet
- Update the Intranet Notice’s payment status in the Intranet after successful validation
- Permanently suspend the Intranet Notice if it is fully paid/partially paid
## High Level Flow

![](data:image/png;base64,)

NOTE: Due to page size limit, the full-sized image is appended.

![](data:image/x-emf;base64,)

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Cron Pull Internet Start | Process initiation | The cron job is triggered every 5 minutes to start pulling updates from the internet. |
| Retrieve internet table eocms_web_txn_detail | Data retrieval | The system queries the internet table for records where is_sync = false and status = S. |
| Any record? | Decision point | Checks if the query retrieved any records. If no records exist, log “no record” and end the process. If records exist, continue. |
| Update/insert to intranet table ocms_web_txn_detail | Data synchronization | Records from the internet table are inserted or updated into the intranet table. |
| Any fail record(s)? (after intranet update) | Decision point | Verifies if there are any failed records during the update/insert process. If failures occur, log an error. If none, continue. |
| Update internet table | Status update | Updates the internet table by setting is_sync = true and upd_date = today for successfully processed records. |
| Any fail record(s)? (after internet update) | Decision point | Checks again if any errors occurred while updating the internet table. If yes, log an error. If no, continue. |
| Update status cron in ocms_batch_job | Process tracking | Updates the status of the cron job in the intranet batch job tracking table ocms_batch_job. |
| End | Completion | The process ends after updating the cron status. |

# Section 3 – Generate Daily Exception Summary Report for Paid Notices

## Use Case

- OCMS generates a daily end-of-day report on payment exceptions from the previous day. 
- The report lists Intranet Notices that encountered the following exceptions during the processing of payment updates from the Internet database:

| Exception Type | Scenario |
| --- | --- |
| Notice was suspended with PS-PRA | Notice was partially paid. |
| Notice was suspended with TS-PAM | The vehicle number in the Internet Notice does not match the Intranet Notice. |
| Double Payment | A second payment was made after the notice was already fully paid. |
| Over Payment | The amount paid exceeds the amount payable. |

- A scheduled cron service will generate the report daily, including Sundays and public holidays.
 

- The report will be emailed to authorised Fine Processing Officers to notify them of the exceptions so that they can follow up on the Notices.
- When there are no exceptions, OCMS will send the report with the remark "No exception records".

| Step | Definition | Brief Description |

| Get list notices | Retrieve eligible notices | Fetches notices with categories PS–PRA, TS–PAM, or with exist in ocms_refund_notice present, using the provided SQL query. |
| Any result? | Decision point for data presence | Checks if any records match the selection criteria. |
| Generate report – exception records | Compile exception details | Creates a report listing and detailing all bad records, pulling specified fields from ocms_web_txn_details, ocms_valid_offence_notice and ocms_refund_notice. |
| Generate report – no exception records | Compile empty report | Creates a report stating “No exception records” when no matching data is found. |

# Section 4 – Generate Paid Notices Report for URA Finance

## Use Case

OCMS generates a monthly report with detail of the parking notices that have been paid in the past month. 

The report lists all Notices that have been updated as paid via the following channels: 

- OCMS Pay Parking Fines eSevice 
- AXS 
- OCMS Staff Portal manual update for offline payment methods such as cash and cheque 
The report will also list all notices that require refund. 

A scheduled cron service will generate the report on the first calendar day of each month, including Sundays and public holidays. 

The report will be emailed to authorised URA Finance Officers so that they can keep track of the monthly collections of parking offence notices at other agencies’ car parks (eg. JTC and MND).
